---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FunctionPlotter from '../../../components/diagrams/FunctionPlotter.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Polynomial Functions" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-10/" backLabel="← Grade 10">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Polynomial Functions</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Polynomial functions and their properties</p>
	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>Higher Powers</h2>
		<p>Polynomials are sums of power functions. Higher degree means more turning points.</p>
		<h3>🧪 Experiment</h3>
		<p>Cubic function with parameter:</p>
	</section>
	<FunctionPlotter client:visible fn={(x, a) => x*x*x - a*x} fnLabel="y = x³ − a·x" showSlider={true} sliderLabel="a" sliderMin={0} sliderMax={4} sliderStep={0.5} yMin={-5} yMax={5} />
	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Properties</h3>
		<ul><li>Degree n → at most n zeros</li><li>Even exponents: y-axis symmetric</li><li>Odd exponents: point-symmetric</li></ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
